    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - PRINCIPLES, OPERATION AND SERVICE - COMPONENT FAILURE - FRONT
        WHEEL SENSOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>FRONT WHEEL SENSOR</title>
        <para>If either the right front or left front wheel sensors are inoperative, the traction control system is
            disabled, however the ABS system is still active. The brake on the wheel with the inoperative sensor will be
            modulated by the controller, using input from the opposite wheel sensor.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
